Your First Stellar Contract - Welcome to the Warrior's Guild!

Lets create a simple "Welcome to the Warriors Guild!" contract using Rust on Stellar.

This contract will greet new warriors when they join your guild.

Heres the code:

#![no_std] use soroban_sdk::{contract, contractimpl, log, symbol_short, Env, Symbol}; #[contract] pub struct WarriorGuildContract; #[contractimpl] impl WarriorGuildContract { pub fn welcome_warrior(env: Env, warrior_name: Symbol) { log!(&env, "Welcome, Warrior {}!", warrior_name); } }

How It Works:

Structure: We define WarriorGuildContract.
Function: The welcome_warrior function takes the environment (env) and the warriors name. It logs a message

For example, if the warrior is "Thorin", the log will display:
"Welcome, Warrior Thorin!"
